First, let's find the symmetric difference A Δ B. The symmetric difference of two sets is the set of elements which are in either of the sets, but not in their intersection.

A Δ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

A = {1, 2, 3}
B = {3, 4, 5}

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
A ∩ B = {3}

A Δ B = {1, 2, 4, 5}

Now, let's find the symmetric difference (A Δ B) Δ C.

(A Δ B) Δ C = ({1, 2, 4, 5} Δ {5, 6, 7})

(A Δ B) Δ C = ({1, 2, 4, 5} ∪ {5, 6, 7}) - ({1, 2, 4, 5} ∩ {5, 6, 7})

{1, 2, 4, 5} ∪ {5, 6, 7} = {1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7}
{1, 2, 4, 5} ∩ {5, 6, 7} = {5}

(A Δ B) Δ C = {1, 2, 4, 6, 7}

So, (A Δ B) Δ C = {1, 2, 4, 6, 7}.
